===Etymology===
Middle English [[bousen]], and connected with Dutch [[buizen]] and German [[bousen#German|bousen]]. (Reference: ''Brewer's Dictionary of Phrase and Fable'', ISBN 0304935700.)

A derivation from U.S. distiller E. C. Booz is false, the term in various forms long pre-dates his entry into the manufacture of booze.

